<br>
Just another opinion of mine is this... <br>
<br>
I understand you're not representing your guild with your views on the camp, but this is something I have always been a firm believer in...<br>
<br>
Everything you say and do while you have your guild tag attached to your name reflects upon your guild as a whole.<br>
<br>
If and when you get your ragefire how you go about it will reflect upon you as a player and your guild.<br>
<br>
The number of guilds and clerics who came to SF while I was "camping" ragefire is almost astounding.  I had guilds come in numbers claiming that they would have no respect for Ragefire as a "camp" and that my time spent was irrelevant because the mob is "FFA", they changed their minds and backed down,  Whether it was because of their morals or because of other reasons it is something that I am still thankful for.  <br>
<br>
I had a cleric from PC parked at the spawn for hours upon hours on the final night of my camp who's intentions were unknown to me at the time.  It kept me on my toes and suprisingly enough when Ragefire spawned I was posed no threat by this cleric, he simply offered his help for the fight.  <br>
<br>
Its amazing how much respect a player and a guild can earn by being kind and respectful to their fellow players no matter how easy it is to be selfish and greedy.  Keep that in mind too.<br>
<br>
