So the camper watches as another cleric completes their epic, possibly gets a little bitter and argues with the opposing guild, then they go back to their camp, all hard done by, hoping that next time RF pops there are forces online that will get there.<br>
<br>
Although it's not nice that someone posts that they've been KSed 5 times it kind of signifies that that guild is not ready to have an extra epic at that moment.<br>
<br>
There were talks for Ragefire and the idea of a camp and rotation fell through. To say that most people wanted a rotation is incorrect. Most wanted it FFA but said they would respect a rotation. This is not the same thing.<br>
<br>
Because of that it remains a FFA mob. As Aishen say's some people respect that camp and that's great, but some guilds have decided that they either cannot or will not camp in SF 24 hours a day for 7 days and that they will engage if nobody else has. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com">
