</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 535<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/24/02 7:02:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3486.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire is FFA</span><hr size=1> Ragefire, like any camp, is officially, according to Verant, FFA.<br>
<br>
Using that belief, whoever spawns him, owns him. And the first person to spawn him, owns him.<br>
<br>
However, the reality is a little different.<br>
<br>
Yes, whoever spawns him, owns him. And yes that is first come first serve...<br>
<br>
But the real question is who has the right to spawn him?<br>
<br>
It is simple common courtesy and respect, really. If someone has gone through the trouble to have the spawnpoint watched 24/7 for days on end, they should be given reasonable time to gather the force and spawn him.<br>
<br>
First group there with sufficient force is BS. Ragefire is a frustrating camp and running over someone who has to put in more effort because they are in a less organized or smaller guild or because he spawns during their guilds off hours is incredibly rude.<br>
<br>
Likewise if you are camping him and when he spawns you know you have no hopes of gathering sufficient force for many many hours, pass on it to someone who can.<br>
<br>
Common Courtesy and respect. Period.<br>
